	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["A 120-microg/cm2 (CD2)n target."]
	}
      ]
     ,"METHOD":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4codes":[{"code":"EDE", "dict":"METHOD", "idict":21,"hlp":"Particle identification by `E/Delta E` measurement"}
	    ,{"code":"COINC", "dict":"METHOD", "idict":21,"hlp":"Coincidence"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" Protons produced by reactions of the 32Si"
		,"beam impinging on (CD2) n target were analyzed by the"
		,"newly developed SOLARIS solenoidal spectrometer. The"
		,"energies and positions at which the protons returned"
		,"to the beam axis were measured using the HELIOS"
		,"array. The projectile-like Si recoils were uniquely"
		,"identified from other reaction channels or un-reacted"
		,"beam components, including the 32S contaminant, by a"
		,"square (5x5 cm2) Si recoil detector telescope with"
		,"quadrant segmentation in the dE. A 20-ns timing"
		,"coincidence between the protons and the Si recoils"
		,"was applied to select the (d,p) reaction channel, to"
		,"separate the S contamination and to reduce the"
		,"background."]
	}
      ]
